dy_navy_upkeep.componentleveltooltip: Amount of money per turn to support your fleets.||Disband ships to reduce this figure.||Fleets are made up of ships.||Each ship has an upkeep cost in its ship details panel.||Ships that are not doing anything are wasting money.||Disband them or move them where they will be useful.

dy_tax_income.componentleveltooltip: Income gained from taxing the wealth of all your provinces.||This number is based on your current tax rate.||If you change the tax rate before the next turn this will change accordingly.

happy.name: happy
happy.tooltip: Under control||The population is either happy, or too scared of you to do anything!||Although both will keep order in your province, a happy population will increase town growth.

neutral.name: neutral
neutral.tooltip: Neutral||The population are neither unhappy nor completely under your control.||You may wish to take steps to improve your control over them, such as increasing repression.

unhappy.name: unhappy
unhappy.tooltip: Unhappy||The population is unhappy and could easily riot and rebel.||Increase repression in this area to keep things from getting worse.

total.componentleveltooltip: This value is taken from the total trade exports detailed above. The amount is added to your {{tr:icon_income}}income per turn.

tx_administration_cost.componentleveltooltip: As your empire grows, administration costs will rise.

tx_income.componentleveltooltip: Income gained from taxing the wealth of all your provinces.||This number is based on your current tax rate.||If you change the tax rate before the next turn this will change accordingly.

component_text.text: You currently have no trade partners. Make trade agreements through diplomacy to gain income from exporting resources.

tx_tax_effects.componentleveltooltip: Changing the tax rate has effects on all provinces in your empire.||The higher your tax rate, the unhappier your population and the slower your provinces will grow.

tx_tax_level.componentleveltooltip: Tax rate slider||Move to the left to decrease the tax rate and the right to increase it. As you move the slider, the tax effects, income and map will update to reflect your changes.

tx_upkeep_mercenary_.componentleveltooltip: Amount of money per turn to support your fleets.||Disband ships to reduce this figure.||Fleets are made up of ships.||Each ship has an upkeep cost in its ship details panel.||Ships that are not doing anything are wasting money.||Disband them or move them where they will be useful.

unsold_income_title.componentleveltooltip: This shows income gained from resources you have not sold or exported.||Create more trade agreements to export more resources and earn more income.

auto_management_holder.componentleveltooltip: Set the budget used for constructing buildings in provinces that have been marked for auto-construction.
